# Project Structure Scanning

## Context
- Before making any changes to imports or file structure
- When adding new features or components
- When refactoring existing code
- When updating dependencies

## Critical Rules
- ALWAYS scan project structure using `list_dir` tool before making changes
- Verify file existence before importing
- Check for correct file paths and exports
- Update MEMORY_BANK.md with any structural changes
- Follow the established directory structure:
  ```
  src/
  ├── app/                    # Next.js app directory
  ├── components/            # Reusable components
  ├── store/                # Redux store
  ├── services/            # API services
  ├── types/              # TypeScript types
  └── lib/               # Utility functions
  ```
- Never assume file locations or exports
- Always verify exports before importing
- Document any new directories or files in MEMORY_BANK.md

## Examples

<example>
// Correct approach
1. First scan the directory:
   list_dir('src/store/auth')
2. Verify file exists and check exports
3. Then make the import:
   import { authSlice } from '@/store/auth/authSlice'
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Incorrect approach
// Making imports without verifying structure
import { authActions } from '@/store/auth/authSlice' // Might not exist
import { useAppDispatch } from '@/store/rootStore' // Wrong path
</example>
